Conditional Display Logic:
When "One-time" selected:

Show: Event Date field
Hide: End Date field

When "Recurring" selected:

Show: Event Date field (labeled "Start Date")
Show: End Date field

Space Dropdown Population:

When user selects Location (school), filter spaces array to show only spaces for that school
Example: If "Lincoln High School" selected → Show only spaces with schoolId: 1

Form Behavior:
On page load:

Auto-populate Name with currentUser.name
Auto-populate Email with currentUser.email
Set Name and Email fields to read-only
Default Request Type to "One-time"
Hide End Date field initially

When Request Type changes:

If "Recurring" selected → Show End Date field, change "Event Date" label to "Start Date"
If "One-time" selected → Hide End Date field, change label back to "Event Date"

When Location changes:

Filter spaces array: spaces.filter(space => space.schoolId === selectedSchoolId)
Update Space dropdown options
Reset Space selection

When Submit clicked:

Validate all required fields
Validate field formats (date, email, number, file size/type)
Check logical constraints (end date > start date, duration > 0, etc.)
If validation fails:

Display error messages next to invalid fields
Highlight invalid fields in red
Scroll to first error
Do not proceed


If validation succeeds:

Collect form data into object
Generate new event ID
Set status to "Pending"
Add to events array
Log simulated emails to console
Display success message: "Request submitted successfully!"
Navigate to Home screen



