10. Data Storage & State Management
10.1 Conceptual Backend
Database Type: Relational database (PostgreSQL conceptually)
Data Organization:
Data is organized into six primary tables:

EVENT table stores all reservation requests
USER table stores user information
SCHOOL table stores school details
SPACE table stores reservable spaces
QUOTE table stores quote information (not implemented in prototype)
REFERENCE_DOCUMENT table stores policy documents

Relationships:

EVENT references USER (via requestorId and reviewerId foreign keys)
EVENT references SCHOOL (via schoolId foreign key)
EVENT references SPACE (via spaceId foreign key)
SPACE references SCHOOL (via schoolId foreign key)
QUOTE references EVENT and USER (not implemented)
REFERENCE_DOCUMENT references USER (uploader)

SQL Operations (Conceptual):
CREATE: INSERT statements add new records
sqlINSERT INTO events (requestor_id, school_id, space_id, event_date, ...)
VALUES (1, 1, 1, '2026-05-15', ...);
READ: SELECT statements retrieve data
sqlSELECT * FROM events 
WHERE status = 'Pending' AND school_id = 1
ORDER BY event_date ASC;
UPDATE: UPDATE statements modify records
sqlUPDATE events 
SET status = 'Approved', comments = 'Looks good', reviewer_id = 1
WHERE event_id = 5;
ARCHIVE: UPDATE status rather than DELETE
sqlUPDATE events 
SET status = 'Denied'
WHERE event_id = 5;
-- Event retained in database for 5 years
