12. Appendix
12.1 Use Case Summaries
UC-Request 1: Submit One-Time Event Request

Actor: Principal (submitting as requestor)
Trigger: User clicks "Submit Request"
Main Flow: Select one-time, fill form, validate, submit, receive confirmation
Postcondition: Request created with Pending status, notifications sent

UC-Request 2: Submit Recurring Event Request

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Submit Request"
Main Flow: Select recurring, fill form with start/end dates, validate, submit
Postcondition: Recurring request created with Pending status

UC-Review 1: Review and Approve Request

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Review Requests" then selects specific request
Main Flow: View details, add comments, click Approve, notifications sent
Postcondition: Request status = Approved, appears on calendar

UC-Review 2: Review and Deny Request

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User reviews pending request
Main Flow: View details, add comments/reason, click Deny
Postcondition: Request status = Denied, archived, removed from calendar

UC-Calendar 1: View Calendar

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Calendar"
Main Flow: System displays events for user's school
Postcondition: Calendar visible with events

UC-Calendar 2: Filter Calendar

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User changes filter selections
Main Flow: Select month, status; system refreshes display
Postcondition: Filtered calendar view

UC-Documentation 1: View Reference Documents

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Documents"
Main Flow: Select document, view in new tab
Postcondition: Document viewed

UC-Documentation 2: View Archived Requests

Actor: Principal
Trigger: User clicks "Archived Requests"
Main Flow: View list, select specific request
Postcondition: Historical request viewed

12.2 Design Goals

Accessibility: Follow ADA guidelines, visual differentiation using color + icons
Compliance: Conform to LCSD policies
Portability: Consistent behavior across devices/browsers
Reliability: Simulate 24/7 availability (conceptually)
Security: Demonstrate role-based access controls (conceptually)
Usability: User-friendly, intuitive, all actions within 3 clicks

12.3 Glossary
Administrative User: Principal, Operations Staff, or Energy Manager with elevated permissions
Approved: Status indicating request has been approved and event is scheduled
Archived: Denied or past events retained for historical reference
Conceptual Backend: Design of how data would be stored/managed if system were fully implemented
Duration: Length of event in hours
Event: A facility reservation request (pending, approved, or denied)
LCSD: Local County School District
One-time Event: Single occurrence reservation
Pending: Status indicating request awaiting review
Principal: School administrator responsible for approving facility use
Prototype: Front-end-only demonstration of system functionality
Quote Pending: Status indicating long-term request requires pricing quote
Recurring Event: Reservation repeating over date range
Reference Document: Policy or guideline document available to all users
Requestor: Person submitting facility use request
Space: Specific reservable area within a school (gym, cafeteria, room)
Status: Current state of request (Pending, Approved, Denied, Quote Pending, Quote Sent)

